Barely 24 hours after a ghastly motor accident involving a truck claimed one life and injured 36 others in Bauchi, another accident involving a Toyota Sienna minibus has claimed one life. A press statement by the Bauchi State Command of the Federal Roads Safety Corps (FRSC) said the accident occurred at the Gumeru village along the ever-busy Bauchi â€“ Kano highway on Thursday. The FRSC said the accident which was caused by a speed limit violation (SPV), involved one private car with REG NO: ABC 755 TS. The car was driven by one Salmanu Tanko. Seven people were involved in the accident out of which one person, a female was killed while six others, 1 male adult, 1 male child, 2 female adults and 2 female children were injured. The victims and the corpse were evacuated and taken to Kafin Madaki General Hospital for treatment and confirmation of death by men of NPF, Kafin Madaki Division as reported.